subSubSection.paragraph:
Capsicum chinense

has been introduced into United States of America (
Bosland and Votava 2000
), Mexico through Cuba (

Gonzalez
Estrada et al. 2010

; 
Ruiz-Lau et al. 2011
; 

Lopez
Castilla et al. 2019

) and Central and South America where is found cultivated or escaped from cultivation; it has also been introduced outside the Americas (Eastern Europe, Africa, Asia: China, Japan, Taiwan, India and others) mainly by Portuguese explorers (
Eshbaugh 1983
; 
Andrews 1993
; 
Meghvansi et al. 2010
).

